body_html: @andrewharp thanks for your reply. I found it is the Op 'DecodeJpeg' problem as mentioned above. I follow @dmirk method to modify the strip_unused.py and finally solve the Op 'DecodeJpeg' problem and run the app successfully. But it seems the label is not correct (displaying 'prediction 0, 1, 2 ... ' rather than 'tulips', 'roses', ...) with the retrained flower model when app runs (update: the reason is the wrong label file name in the LABEL_FILE string). I will work on that the next day. Finally, thank @andrewharp @dmirk and other participants in this post.
